post_text: Today is September 11 and marks the 19th anniversary of the worst terrorist attack on US soil in our history. Our freedoms and way of life were attacked by 19 terrorists. Our country lost over 3000 innocent citizens on that day. We encourage you to take some time today, and this weekend, to remember those who lost their lives and reflect on the sacrifice our first responders and military personnel make each day to keep us safe.

Good afternoon,

We are aware Freeburg High School has switched to all remote learning until at least August 26 due to staff being quarantined. We have been told none of our students or staff has come into contact with any of the quarantined individuals.

We are continuing with in-person learning on Monday with Group "A."

If anything changes, we will send messages via TeacherEase, Facebook, phone calls, and Twitter.

Thank you, and have a great weekend. Be safe and mask up.

post_text:
Good afternoon,

I have bittersweet news to share. Our Secretary at the Primary Center, Tracy Kessler, is retiring, effective immediately.

As you may or may not know, she recently became a grandmother for the first time and felt now was a good time to retire. She was initially planning to work for about three more years but has decided to retire now. Who can blame her with everything going on?

I don't think anyone would disagree when I say Tracy was the lifeblood of the Primary Center. We would often joke Tracy runs the Primary Center. This was mostly true. Her friendliness and compassion toward our students, staff, and parents were her hallmarks.

We will begin looking for her replacement immediately. Please join me in sharing your good wishes as she enters retirement. The Primary Center won't be the same without her.

post_text:
Good afternoon,

We have bittersweet news to share. Nurse Ramona Stein has tendered her letter of resignation, effective later this month.

She has been offered an excellent career opportunity that was too good for her to pass up.

We don't need to tell any of you what she has meant for our district for the past ten years. Later this month, she would have been with us for exactly ten years. Her compassion and dedication to the well-being of our students were second to none. She would do anything for our students.

We will begin looking for her replacement immediately. Please join me in sharing your good wishes and gratitude for all she has done as she begins this new chapter of her life. Our district family is losing a treasured employee and person.

post_text:
Freeburg District 70 is now accepting applications for the 2020/21 More at Four Pre-K program. Applications will be available through July 1. Any children who live in the Freeburg School District and will be 3 or 4 by August 31, 2020 are eligible to apply. Only those families who complete the application process will be considered for enrollment in the More at Four Program. Enrollment this year will be extremely limited.

The process will be contactless and will begin with a phone interview and completion of necessary paperwork. In-person developmental screenings will be held later this summer. For more information or to receive an application, call the Freeburg District #70 Office, 618-539-3188.

post_text: Happy Monday District 70!! We hope all of you are doing well. We are all curious about what everyone is doing since we don't get to talk with you in the school building. Kindergarten registration for the upcoming 2020-2021 school year will be on February 12 from 4 pm to 7 pm and on February 13 from 9 am - 11 am. You can come to register at the Elementary School Office located at 408 South Belleville Street. Parents/Guardians will need to bring the following:

Birth Certificate
Lease Agreement (if renting) or most recent tax bill (if you own).
Three (3) other pieces of mail with name and address.
Custody Papers, if applicable.

For questions, please call 539-3188.
